»CL9:----------------------> »CL8:welcome

»CL7:              We invite you to the third annual
              Distance party! Distance '99 will be
              arranged at Eikeli Videregående Skole in
              Bærum, close to the center of Oslo,
              Norway. The party begins on the 30th of
              September and ends the 3rd of October
              1999. This party is the third Distance
              party in the Distance history and will
              this time be bigger and better than any
              previous Distance party. Everyone can
              come, sceners, quakers, rc, foreigners,
              presidents, elvis, as well as nerds and
              swedes. Just grab your partygear and come
              as you are.
























              Entry
                   Girls/ladies/etc : 150 nkr
                   Boys/men/wannabies : 300 nkr
                   Visitors from outside norway : 150
                   Extraterrestials / Aliens : Access
                   denied

              Tickets can be ordered through
              "Billettservice", just call 815 33 133 to
              order. There will only be room for app.
              350 people, so you better hurry if you
              want to save a seat! Note, tickets not
              available before July 1.

              Note that if the hall gets crowdy, only
              people who have paid in advance gets in.
              If you are a foreigner, you may pay at
              the entrance.






















»CL9:----------------------> »CL8:features

»CL0:              Network

»CL7:                   There will be a party network, set
                   up by the organizers. Network cards
                   will be sold at the partyplace.

»CL0:              Internet

»CL7:                   There will be internet access
                   through the party network

»CL0:              Movies

»CL7:                   We will probably be continuosly
                   showing new movies in a separate
                   room.






















»CL0:              Sleeping area

»CL7:                   For those who need to take a nap,
                   there will be a separate, quiet
                   area designated sleeping, close to
                   the main party-halls. Also, toilets
                   and showers will be available
                   throughout the party.

»CL0:              Surprise compos

»CL7:                   Yes, there will be surprisecompos.

»CL0:              IRC channel

»CL7:                   There will be an official
                   IRC-channel running during the party
                   for partychats. [ will be announced
                   at the party ]





















»CL0:              On-stage activities

»CL7:                   We will continously be showing
                   useful information on the bigscreen,
                   showing everything from practical
                   informations to compo deadlines.
                   In-between, we will be showing some
                   good old demos. Also, a resident DJ
                   will play on friday evening.

»CL0:              Partykiosk / cafeteria

»CL7:                   There will be a 24h kiosk in the
                   partyhall, selling coca cola, pizza,
                   red bull and stuff.

























»CL9:----------------------> »CL8:how to get there

»CL7:              Distance is this time held at Eikeli vgs,
              which is located at Bispeveien 10 in
              Bærum, just outside Oslo. It's very easy
              to get to the hall, several trains and
              buses stop almost outside the door. The
              easiest way to get to the hall is to take
              subway line 2 towards Østerås and get off
              at Østerås station. The way to the party
              place is marked from there.





























»CL0:              By car

              From south (coming in to Oslo from E-18 Drammen)

»CL7:                   Follow E-18 until you see a sign
                   that says "lysaker / fornebu". Drive
                   off the road (use the intersection,
                   for gods sake), then follow the
                   signs to "Jar" Follow the road a few
                   kilometers, you're supposed to cross
                   two bridges. When you've crossed the
                   last bridge, take left then right
                   again. Now just follow the road for
                   a few kilometers, you're supposed to
                   pass a Shell-station on your left
                   hand. When you've passed that one,
                   you're getting close. Now look for
                   "Eikeli Videregående Skole" on your
                   right hand, a large brown building.
                   Take right and follow the road




















                   called "Bispeveien", and then turn
                   left again. You're now at Distance :]

»CL0:              From north or east (coming to Oslo following E-6)

»CL7:                   Drive till you reach Oslo (Capitol
                   of Norway, remember?). Then follow
                   road called E-6 until you see the
                   signs leading to "Drammen" (E-18).
                   You're supposed to drive through the
                   center of Oslo and continue west.
                   Drive until you see a sign leading
                   to "Jar" on your right hand. Follow
                   the road a few kilometers, you're
                   supposed to cross two bridges. When
                   you've crossed the last bridge, take
                   left then right again. Now just
                   follow the road for a few
                   kilometers, you're supposed to pass
                   a Shell-station on your left hand.




















                   When you've passed that one, you're
                   getting close. Now look for "Eikeli
                   Videregående Skole" on your right
                   hand, a large brown building. Take
                   right and follow the road called
                   "Bispeveien", and then turn left
                   again. You're now at Distance :]


»CL0:              By train

»CL7:                   Travel by train to Oslo S, then take
                   the subway line 2 towards Østerås
                   from Oslo S and get of at Østerås
                   station. The way to the party place
                   is marked from there.
























»CL0:              By plane
»CL7:                   Travel by plane to Oslo, then take
                   the airport bus to Oslo S and follow
                   the directions for train from there.

»CL0:              Bustrips
»CL7:                   If you are arranging a bustrip to
                   Distance, and would like to be on
                   this list, please send a mail to
                   trasker@online.no. There might be
                   some freebies involved. :)





























»CL9:----------------------> »CL8:compos

»CL0:              a few selected words

»CL7:                   This is what distance is really
                   about; demoscene compos. Listed
                   below are the compos, and we're
                   serving hard cash prices to the
                   winners in the major compos. [note;
                   the money-prices may depend on the
                   number of party attendants and party
                   income] If you wish to attend one or
                   more of these compos, you must have
                   been registered at the main party
                   database after paying your entrance
                   fee.
























»CL7:                   Basically, all productions will be
                   shown / played. If we recieve a lot
                   of entries, a jury will make a
                   selection. [especially multichannel
                   and 4 channel if nessesary]

                   There will be a votesession that
                   will finalize the results from these
                   compos

»CL0:              general rules

                »CL1: o»CL7: All entries will be released after
                   the party.
                »CL1: o»CL7: FILE_ID.DIZ must be included.
                »CL1: o»CL7: *.NFO must be included on demo and
                   intro entries.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Delivered diskettes will not be
                   returned.





















»CL0:              compo machines

»CL0:                   PC
»CL7:                   Pentium 233
                   VESA 2.0 gfx-card
                   32MB RAM
                   Gravis Ultrasound with 1MB
                   SoundBlaster 16

»CL0:                   Amiga
»CL7:                   A1200 with 68060 accelerator
                   16MB RAM




























»CL0:              PC DEMO

                »CL1: o»CL7: Have a maximum filesize of 6MB,
                   including datafiles.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Max. 16MB RAM.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Must support GUS, SoundBlaster
                   and/or nosound.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Exit by escape at any time.
                »CL1: o»CL7: One entry per coder.

»CL0:              AMIGA DEMO

                »CL1: o»CL7: Have a maximum filesize of 6MB,
                   including datafiles.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Must be able to run on 030/040/060
                   AGA Amigas with 8MB Fast RAM or more.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Max. 16MB RAM.
                »CL1: o»CL7: Exit by left mouse button at any time.
                »CL1: o»CL7: One entry per coder.





















»CL0:              PC 64k INTRO

                »CL1: o»CL7: Have a maximum filesize of 64K
                   (65536 bytes), including datafiles. :)
                »CL1: o»CL7: Otherwise the same rules as PC demo.
                »CL1: o»CL7: One entry per coder.

»CL0:              AMIGA 64k INTRO

                 »CL1:o »CL7:Have a maximum filesize of 64K
                   (65536 bytes), including datafiles.

                 »CL1:o »CL7:Otherwise the same rules as Amiga demo.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per coder.


























»CL0:              PC 4k INTRO

                 »CL1:o »CL7:Must have a maximum filesize of 4K
                   (4096 bytes).
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Otherwise the same rules as PC demo.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per coder.

»CL0:              AMIGA 4k INTRO

                 »CL1:o »CL7:Must have a maximum filesize of 4K
                   (4096 bytes).
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Otherwise the same rules as Amiga demo.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per coder.



























»CL0:              24-BIT PIXEL

                 »CL1:o »CL7:We accept pictures in the following
                   formats: IFF (LBM), TGA, PCX, BMP,
                   GIF, JPG.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Max. resolution 800x600 (24bit).
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Photopictures will be discarded.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per artist.

»CL0:              RAYTRACE

                 »CL1:o »CL7:We accept pictures in the following
                   formats: IFF (LBM), TGA, PCX, BMP,
                   GIF, JPG.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Max. resolution 800x600 (24bit).
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Photopictures will be discarded.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per artist.























»CL0:              MUSIC 4-CHANNEL

                 »CL1:o »CL7:Only modules in Protracker format
                   (MOD) is accepted.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Max size 1MB unpacked.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:All contributions will be played in
                   mono with Hippoplayer on Amiga.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per musician.

»CL0:              MUSIC MULTICHANNEL

                 »CL1:o »CL7:We accept modules in the following
                   formats: XM, MOD, S3M, IT.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Max. 32 channels.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:Must be playable on a 1MB GUS.
                 »CL1:o »CL7:All contributions will be played on
                   a 1MB GUS with FastTracker (XM and
                   MOD) and ImpulseTracker (IT and S3M).
                 »CL1:o »CL7:One entry per musician.





















